description.1: Trapped in an apocalyptic future with Pluto, God of Death, Sif and Thor find themselves in dire need of back-up. In true god-like fashion, Zeus makes his sweeping entrance. Is the King of the Gods here to support the Asgardians, or Pluto? Back on Asgard, Balder continues to struggle with stray thoughts of Karnilla, the Norn Queen.
description.2: The Invisible Girl returns! After shaking a nasty case of brainwashing, the entire team reunites in Latveria to destroy Doom's robots. And if the FF should fail...Latveria will fall!
description.4: The Shocker's on a crime spree and Spider-Man better be up to the task to stop him. Plus, Peter's relationship with Gwen Stacy gets further strained as the stress from his Spider-Man life seeps over to his personal life.
description.5: Egghead has a new orbital death ray, and he's making demands of the United States government.
description.6: While the members of Hydra celebrate the death of Captain America, Madame Hydra recounts her early years in Europe.
description.7: Captain Marvel must put aside alternative plans to confront Yon-Rogg about throwing him into space!
description.8: Times Square on New Year's Eve is one of the most bustling places on Earth - especially when it's full of monsters and warriors from ancient times! Only one man can find out what has caused this blast from the past - Doctor Strange, the Sorcerer Supreme!
description.9: Karthon uncovers a deadly secret about Naga and a member of his family. Namor's temper lands him in hot water.
description.10: With the Hate-Monger at last defeated, Nick and co. finally get a much-needed break - until HYDRA rears its many heads yet again!
description.15: The Mandarin and Sandman are aligned against Hulk! With the oncoming evil multiplied, can the Gamma Green Giant withstand the storm? Especially when Betty Ross is used as a pawn in the Mandarin's game?
description.16: Iron Man rockets into action to stop the Controller, a villain with the ability to control the minds of those around? Can Iron Man stop the evildoer or will he just become another addition to the Controller's collection?
description.18: When Sif goes missing during a mission on Earth, Thor investigates. What the Thunder God uncovers disturbs him greatly; an atomic research site has been infiltrated by mutated beings. Is Lady Sif's disappearance connected to this strange event? Enter Pluto, the Roman god of Death!
description.19: Trapped in Latveria, Reed, Johnny, Ben and Crystal become the reluctant guests of Doctor Doom! And the FF is in for some culture shock- especially when Doom unleashes an android army on his own people! This is no diplomatic mission...it's all out war!
description.20: At the mercy of Quicksilver's fury! After deciding to give up his life as a super villain, Quicksilver looks to join the Avengers. But when they're not at the Avengers Mansion, he believes he can get in their good graces by bringing in New York's greatest criminal....Spider-Man?!
description.21: Once the smoke clears from Cap's battle with Hyrdra, his bullet-ridden uniform is pulled out of the water. Is Captain America dead?
description.22: Captain Marvel and Black Widow fight against the Man-Slayer, a Communist robot!
description.23: Will this be the issue that restores Surfer's faith in humanity?!
description.24: Note: this is a reprint of Amazing Spider-Man Annual (1964) #2. Doctor Strange and Spider-Man team up against the evil sorcerer Xandu and his henchmen after they steal the Wand of Watoomb from the Sanctum Sanctorum!
description.26: What will Karthon the Quester do with the Serpent Crown?
description.27: Nick Fury and S.H.I.E.L.D. at last have their final showdown with the Hate-Monger!
description.29: Daredevil vs. a Killer Automaton! The Man Without Fear is put through the wringer by Biggie Benson's hired robot. Karen and Foggy have realizations about their relationship with Matt. When Starr Saxon's robot turns on Biggie, will DD rise to the occasion or let the convict fall?
description.30: Bruce Banner's in deep trouble! Hurtling through space in a capsule without oxygen, Banner's life is measured down to mere moments. But will Bruce's scientific ingenuity be his saving grace? Plus, Hulk takes on Sandman!
description.31: The Mandarin has Iron Man all figured, and is ready to expose him to the world! But can the Iron Playboy convince the mandarin that things aren't what they seem? Find out in this thrilling issue, when the Invincible Iron Man is unmasked!
description.33: Following his victory over Galactus, Thor receives a hero's welcome back to Asgard. Odin investigates the origin of Galactus, curious about how such a powerful cosmic entity was spawned. Will the birth of Galactus, Eater of Worlds, be finally revealed?
description.34: The Fantastic Four infiltrate Latveria on the orders of S.H.I.E.L.D. But given the tyrannical ruler of the country, the team encounters more than they bargained for. The FF versus Doctor Doom and his horde of Servo-Guards!
description.36: Nick's holiday vacation is cut short when an old menace rises yet again - the Hate-Monger!? How could this sinister foe possibly be able to cheat death so easily?
description.37: When the Kingpin escapes from prison, he won't be the only problem Spider-Man has as he struggles with being Public Enemy #1, despite trying to be a hero.
description.38: Half of the Avengers team is stranded in Antarctica. Suddenly, they are surrounded by Wakandan troops. Will Black Panther's former sway with his countrymen get the Avengers out of this mess?
description.39: Nearly all of Jim Steranko's covers could make this list, but it's the timelessness of this Cap cover that shines on.
description.40: The battle continues as the Kree come for Mar-Vell's life!
description.41: Doctor Strange pairs up with the Black Knight and travels to the realm of Tiboro!
description.42: We all know the immense battles Prince Namor has endured...but what happens when the United States Navy is at his tail?
description.43: Loki, a master of deception, convinces Surfer that Thor is up to no good! An epic battle between two powerful forces commences!
description.44: In a shocking twist, Stephen Strange discovers the secret identity of Asmodeus!
description.46: Prince Namor has many obstacles in his way in an attempt to capture the Serpent Crown...one of them being the creature named Barracuda!
description.47: The HATE-MONGER returns! But he was killed in his showdown with the Fantastic Four, wasn't he? How can he possibly still be alive?
description.48: Tired of being Daredevil, Matt Murdock decides to pack up the super hero suit. Before the dust can settle, Daredevil's attacked by Starr Saxon's robot! But who put out the hit? Willie Lincoln to the (unexpected) rescue.
description.49: Hulk vs. the Galaxy Master! Hulk enters into galactic warfare with an overlord of an alien race.
description.50: The Mandarin has returned, and he knows the true identity of Iron Man! Read to see what happens when Tony Stark runs out of idea! Plus: you won't believe the ending!
description.52: Galactus and Ego the Living Planet, trapped in a cosmic duel! With his enemy occupied, will Thor and the Recorder be able to pull the wool over Galactus' eyes? Plus, meet the Wanderers, an alien race of nomads intent on finding a new home after they're homeland was destroyed by Galactus. Will Thor be the savior that the Wanderers so desperately need?
description.54: Reed, Johnny and Ben remain helpless against Maximus and his band of followers. But with the combined might of the Inhuman Royal Family, the FF might be able to save humanity from Maximus' hypno-gun!
description.56: Scouring the city for the Kingpin, Spider-Man's on a mission to retrieve the ancient tablet that was stolen. But will the police look to Spider-Man as an ally...or a menace?
description.57: While tending to the Vision, Black Panther and Hawkeye are visited by an astral form of Dr. Strange! What does the Sorcerer Supreme need from the Avengers? And why is Black Knight in danger?
description.58: When a skirmish between the Hulk and Captain America leaves Rick Jones injured, Cap is left with a choice: bring Jones to safety or pursue the Jade Giant?
description.59: After failing another attempt in proving his worth to the Kree by forging an alliance with the Organization, Ronan orders to have Mar-Vell executed.
description.61: Foggy Nelson, District Attorney! Foggy wins the position of D.A. in a "landslide election", leading to much upheaval at Nelson & Murdock. Karen Page returns to the law office, in part to rekindle her romance with Matt. But what does the villainous Stilt-Man have to do with the new D.A.?
description.62: Bruce Banner lies dying in the Savage Land, with only Ka-Zar and Zabu as allies...until a strange alien race kidnaps and revives the Hulk! Enter the Galaxy Master!
description.63: It's the battle of the century! Iron Man versus the Hulk! Who will win? Brute strength against genius intellect!
description.65: Thor versus the greatest cosmic power of all- Galactus! How did the Asgardian god become embroiled in galactic warfare? And will Odin let his son, and heir to the throne, engage in life-or-death battle? It's an all-out space war, as Thor takes on his most dangerous foe yet!
description.67: Maximus the Mad takes on the Fantastic Four...and all of humanity! Crystal seeks permission from her Inhuman family to join the FF in full membership. But upon arriving in the Inhumans' Hidden Land, the team is attacked by Alpha Primitives!
description.68: When the Kingpin of Crime looks to steal an ancient tablet, will Spider-Man be up to the task to stop him and his henchmen?
description.69: Captain America is shocked to receive an invitation to the wedding of Wasp and Yellowjacket. The wedding is soon interrupted, however, by the arrival of Princess Python and the Ringmaster!
description.71: Captain Marvel finds himself in a battle between the Cyberex and the Aakon!
description.72: SUPREMUS strikes! A shunned mad scientist with a powerful exoskeleton vows revenge on humanity, and even Nick Fury can't stop him all on his own!
description.73: Aware that Clea is under Asmodeus' control, Strange allows her to steal the Book of Vishanti so he can follow her back to his enemy's base.
description.74: The Spell of the Serpent has been cast upon all of Atlantis, including Prince Namor!
description.75: The First Appearance of Mephisto!  Silver Surfer's contempt for the human race seems to be growing by the second. Humankind's rejection will become his fuel to destroying us all!
description.76: Sons of Satannish leader Asmodeus disguises himself as Wong, and enters Doctor Strange's Sanctum Sanctorum...
description.78: Time for a special guest -- The Thing! Unfortunately, the Sub-Mariner isn't nearly as excited to see this Fantastic Four member as we are...
description.79: The showdown in the Savage Land comes to a head! The evil Umbu is determined to let the artifact wreak havoc on Earth's rotation, and the only thing left that can stop it is the Incredible Hulk!
description.80: Nick Fury - ASSASSINATED? When enemy agents inject him with a deadly slow-acting poison, Fury enters a race against the clock to get to S.H.I.E.L.D. and get the cure…all while the poison drives him slowly mad!
description.81: Mysterio has miniaturized Spider-Man and placed him in a tiny amusement park. Can Spider-Man survive this deadly Hall of Mirrors?
description.82: Enter the Yellowjacket! Who is this new costumed menace terrorizing New York and the Avengers? And how does he have personal knowledge about the team?
description.83: Sharon Carter is the prisoner of the Trapster! Will the machinations of the Trapster be too much for Captain America to overcome?
description.84: Mar-Vell uncovers the truth to Walter Lawson's past but it's one big, humanoid secret.
description.85: Daredevil does his part for the troops, when he visits American soldiers in Vietnam. While there, DD meets a blind soldier with a story all his own. Will Willie Lincoln require the assistance of Daredevil, or the legal counsel of Matt Murdock?
description.86: While Iron Man fights the Gladiator to protect Janice Cord, Whitney Frost attacks Stark Industries to still all of Tony Stark's high tech weapons! Will she succeed? Find out in this action-packed issue!
description.88: The mystery of Donald Blake revealed! After seeking answers from Odin about his true identity, Donald Blake gets more than he bargained for. Is Doctor Blake the true Odinson? And if so, how did Thor become trapped in the body of a mortal man?
description.90: Crystal of the Inhumans joins the team! Following Sue's maternity leave, the Fantastic Four...are three. Crystal steps up to the challenge of becoming a full time member, and just in time too- the Wizard's launched an attack on the Baxter Building!
description.92: Spider-Man faces off against the Master of Illusions himself, Mysterio!
description.93: Vision is put through a series of tests to gain membership with the Avengers.
description.94: Captain America's mind is under attack by one of his most nefarious enemies...his shrink? It's a battle for sanity when Cap goes toe to toe with Dr. Faustus.
description.95: To prove his loyalty, Mar-Vell must unleash a virus on a human town!
description.96: An asteroid is hurtling towards Earth, and only Nick Fury can stop it! But shadowy forces will stop at nothing to ensure the asteroid finds its target, and they have Nick in their sights!
description.97: Were Richard and Mary Parker traitors or heroes? Peter seeks to answer this question. But he may have to go through a Red Skull or two...
description.98: Stephen quickly realizes that Clea may not be able to assimilate to life on earth. Later, he and Victoria are tricked into visiting London by a satanic disciple.
description.99: How will the Sub-Mariner perform beyond his depths, on the surface world instead of the oceans he rules?

5.text: Adversaries for years, the Falcon and Henry Gyrich are on the verge of fighting it out! What role will the sinister Scarecrow play in the unfolding drama?

11.text: Hoop-la!! The incredible planet that we heard from someone is way cooler than Earth! Don't blame it on us if it isn't though! All of that packed into "The Origin of the Simple Surfer"! AND many more spoofy stories including "Dr. Deranged Vs. Deadpan" and "Liltin' Limericks"!

12.text: The Avengers must make an emergency landing over the Arctic after the Panther’s ship malfunctions. Meanwhile, Hank Pym confesses to the team that he is struggling with his schizophrenic personality, Yellowjacket.

13.text: Matt, reeling from his battle against Saxon’s robot, starts hallucinating and blacking out. Who better to exploit this weakness than Starr Saxon himself? Daredevil has pulled the plug on Saxon’s finest creation, and now he will feel the robot maker’s wrath!

38.text: Jack of Hearts and Ant-Man, two quarrelsome recruits caught in their own crises! One faces his father's secrets, the other his daughter's fate!

39.text: Nearly all of Jim Steranko's covers could make this list, but it's the timelessness of this Cap cover that shines on.

53.text: The X-Men are under attack from Blastarr!

55.text: Ever thought, "hey I want to see a Not Brand Echh spoof of The Beatles?" No? Nobody? Well, too bad we have one here for you anyway in "Sgt. Fury's Lonely Hearts Club Band" and you'll LOVE it! PLUS: a Frankenstein monster with not-so-nice breath in "Frankenstein Sicksty-Nine!"

57.text: The team gains new international status, but will everyone accept it? Avengers come and go as the new lineup is established and new threats await!

66.text: Who is Erik the Red? Will he join Magneto?

69.text: The Avengers vs. Scorpio and the Brotherhood of the Ankh! Will even turning the villains' own forces against them be enough?

82.text: Yellowjacket and the Wasp, trapped in extradimensional torment! To rescue them, the Avengers must appeal to a cosmic entity's good side...literally!

89.text: Discover Lorna Dane's accursed lineage! Also, the X-Men duke it out with Magneto!

91.text: "King Konk '68", naturally, is the remake of King Kong that we needed but we didn't deserve. And of course, you can expect your regular Not Brand Echh crew to make an appearance as well! PLUS: many more tales including "How To Be A Comic Book Artist!", "Super-Hero Day Dreams" and more!

93.text: The world's leaders have disappeared, and only the Avengers can guide Earth out of chaos! But the path leads to an extradimensional realm ruled by an unexpected adversary!
